<br>
The only &quot;normal&quot; animals that I know of that have faction are those in Surefall Glade and Kithicor Forest.  (There are no wolves in Surefall Glade, btw, just bears.)  Many rangers and druids won't kill bears or wolves because they /consider amiably.  I've noticed, however, that wolves in Misty Thicket will assist bixies when they're attacked, even against druids.  I guess they see something in those annoying little buggers that the rest of us don't.  /giggle<br>
<br>
Fighting bears or wolves near druids near the circle of stones in North Karana (I'm not certain about those in West Commonlands) will incur their wrath as well, even if you're only defending yourself.  <br>
<br>
Holly Windstalker in Qeynos Hills will attack you if she sees you fighting a wolf or bear, whether they be &quot;healthy&quot; or rabid, or looting the corpse of a dead one.  Cros Treewind would, too, but I believe he longer roams QH.  I heard that he was perma killed.  /shrug<br>
<br>
